uswdsNotifications:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
✉ USWDS Notifications
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.0.2: We changed the names of some settings and mixins.

- $theme-title-font-size → $theme-display-font-size
- @include title → @include display
- @include typeset-title → @include typeset-display
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.2.0: We changed the names of some settings.

- $theme-navigation-width → $theme-header-min-width
- $theme-megamenu-logo-text-width → $theme-header-logo-text-width
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.4.0: If your component settings aren't working as expected, make
sure you're importing the components settings in your Sass entry
point (often styles.scss) with `@import 'uswds-theme-components'`.
A bug in 2.0 omitted that import.
- We added `$theme-show-notifications: true` to general settings
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.5.0:
- We updated to Dart Sass for compiling. Consider updating your own
  build process using `uswds-gulp` as a guide.
- We upgraded our aXe accessibility testing from 2.6.1 to 3.4.1 and
  improved the accessibility of our markup in the process.
  This introduces minor changes to the markup of 5 components and 
  our documentation template:
  - banner: is now a <section> instead of a <div> with the ARIA 
    label `Official government website`
  - footer: nav includes the ARIA label of `Footer navigation`
  - graphic-list: uses <h2> as a heading default instead of <h3> 
  - hero: includes the ARIA label of `Introduction`
  - search: the search form is given the ARIA role of `search`
  - documentation template: includes only the main content in the 
    <main> element. The nav is no longer treated as an <aside>.
- Now state tokens (like 'warning') can can accept non-token
  colors, just as we introduced for theme colors in 2.4.0.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.5.1:
- CSSO's forceMediaMerge wasn't exporting media queries in the
  expected order, so we're disabling it for more reliable CSS
  output. We recommend that teams remove any media query sorting
  added with forceMediaMerge.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.6.0:
- We updated the markup of usa-search. Existing markup will still
  work, but we recommend updating to the newest markup.
- We updated some color token values and filled out the vivid color
  families. This is not a breaking change, but be aware that there
  may be some subtle changes.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.7.0:
- We added new usa-button-group, usa-card, usa-character-count, and
  usa-combo-box components.
- We updated our guidance and code for numeric fields to use `text`
  rather than `number` inputs with an `inputmode` of `numeric`.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.7.1:
- We added `not dead` to our autoprefixer settings and now use a 
  `.browserslistrc` file for these options.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.8.0:
- We updated the text of the gov banner and its settings.
  Please see the full release notes for more information and update
  your project's banner as soon as possible.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.9.0:
- We updated the formatting of `usa-legend`. If you use a visible 
  legend and wish to preserve the old styling, add a 
  `usa-legend--large` modifier to the element.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.10.0:
- We updated the Spanish language link to USAGov in the identifier. 
  The link should now read 'Visite USAGov en Español'. 
- We improved the accessibility of SVG images in the banner. 
  See the full release notes for more information.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.10.1:
- We updated the `$theme-breadcrumb-background-color` default
  to `default` from `'white'`. 
- We updated the `$theme-alert-icon-size` default to `5` from `4`.
- [Footer] We updated `usa-footer__logo-heading` to use a `p`.
  instead of an `h3`. 
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.11.0:
- We updated some settings defaults:
  $theme-alert-icon-size: 4 (was 5)
  $theme-table-border-color: default (was 'ink')
  $theme-table-header-text-color: default (was 'ink')
  $theme-table-stripe-text-color: default (was 'ink')
  $theme-table-text-color: default (was 'ink')
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.11.2:
- We deprecated the `$theme-site-max-width` variable. We're using
  `$theme-grid-container-max-width` instead.
- We replaced the `thumb_down_off_alt` icon with `thumb_down_alt`
  in our default icon sprite.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.12.0:
- We deprecated three settings:
  $theme-input-tile-background-color-selected
  $theme-input-tile-border-color
  $theme-input-tile-border-color-selected
  Each of these is now calculated automatically
- We updated some settings defaults:
  $theme-color-success-dark: green-cool-50v (was green-cool-50)
  $theme-color-success-darker: green-cool-60v (was green-cool-80)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.12.2:
- As a security precaution, we're now sanitizing text passed into 
  Tooltip. Tooltip no longer supports markup in its content.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
2.13.0:
  BREAKING CHANGES:
- We made a couple breaking changes to support the accessibility
  of icon-only buttons. See complete release notes:
  https://github.com/uswds/uswds/releases/tag/v2.13.0
- We updated the markup of the small Search button to include its 
  magnifying glass icon as an inline image instead of as a 
  background image.
  See the release notes for the updated markup.
- We updated the markup of the social icons in the Footer 
  to use inline images instead of background images.
  See the release notes for the updated markup.
